-- Regression: REG-02 crash-canary for static method dispatch
-- (Type.method via stdlib namespace form).
--
-- **Motivating Incident.** Phase 37-02's collect_mono_enums_node
-- walker crashed on if/elif/else lowering because of a locally-
-- shadowed struct typedef. Static/namespace-style calls
-- (`Math.sign(x)`, `Net.tcp_listen(...)`) lower through
-- Iron_FuncRef + Iron_CallExpr where the func_ref carries a
-- type-prefixed name that resolves at typecheck time to a free
-- function on the stdlib type namespace. Walker cases that handle
-- the generic CALL kind but mis-read the func_ref payload silently
-- drop the type-qualified prefix and dispatch to the wrong function.
-- Phase 66 added PROT-04 blind-cast rewrites for FUNC_REF sites and
-- -Werror=switch-enum globally; this canary is the runtime regression
-- net for namespace-style CALL dispatch.
--
-- **Layout Diagram.** Iron v0.1.4-alpha exposes namespace-style
-- static calls via the stdlib `Math`, `Net`, `TcpListener`,
-- `TcpSocket`, `Time` types. Each resolves via:
--   Iron_CallExpr { callee: Iron_FuncRef { type_name, method_name },
--                   args[] }
-- Walker cases that fail to recurse into `type_name` drop the
-- namespace prefix; cases that ignore `method_name` dispatch to the
-- default function in the namespace.
--
-- **Fix Summary.** Phase 67-08 added this fixture as a REG-02 crash
-- canary. Uses `Math.sign(x)` because it is the only stdlib static
-- call that returns Int (every other Math.* returns Float, which is
-- platform-format-sensitive in println). Note that Iron does not yet
-- expose the `static` keyword for user-defined types -- user-space
-- static method dispatch is synthesized at typecheck time via
-- `func Type.method(args)` without a self parameter, but that idiom
-- is not uniformly supported across Iron v0.1.4-alpha; this canary
-- uses the documented stdlib form. CI integration: runs in both
-- Debug and Release via Phase 66-04's build-and-test-release job.
--
-- **Severity.** H (regression potential) -- static/namespace calls
-- are used by every Iron program that touches stdlib Math, Net,
-- Time, TcpListener, or TcpSocket.

import math

func main() {
  val s1 = Math.sign(-7.5)    -- -1
  val s2 = Math.sign(0.0)     -- 0
  val s3 = Math.sign(4.2)     -- 1
  val sum = s1 + s2 + s3      -- 0
  println("s1: {s1}")
  println("s2: {s2}")
  println("s3: {s3}")
  println("sum: {sum}")
}
